From: Mono OpenWrt Integration <integration@mono.local>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 08:00:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] net/crypto: add narrow ASK IPsec offload plumbing

Add the kernel-side contract needed by ASK CDX/CMM to program and select
hardware IPsec SAs without enabling the broad vendor CPE fast-path switch.

The patch adds ASK SA handles to XFRM state, a narrow NETLINK_KEY command
path for CMM/CDX offload events, IPv4/IPv6 Kconfig symbols, native ESP
offload handoff for marked packets, inbound SEC submission, IPsec skb
metadata preservation, and the SEC handoff plumbing needed for PPPoE/VLAN
tunnel paths.  Linux remains authoritative for routing, firewall, conntrack,
XFRM policy, and fallback.

Native ASK IPsec offload still uses the XFRM state MTU as the packet-size
authority: forwarded GSO packets are clamped before software segmentation,
and oversized DF tunnel packets take the normal PMTU error path instead of
being handed to SEC oversized.

Keep the CAAM IPsec protocol data block layouts byte-exact for SEC by packing
the IPsec PDB structs.  This is the narrow IPsec-only part of the vendor SDK
change needed so descriptor fields such as the outbound ESP SPI land at the
offsets expected by hardware.

